cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO

This paper discusses the application of image restoration and enhancement techniques to improve automatic visual recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also evaluates the impact of these techniques on deep learning-based object classification approaches, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of a benchmark dataset for assessing the impact of image restoration and enhancement on automatic visual recognition also relates to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
